This year I got the opportunity to Co-Host the Dancing with the Stars Live Tour and it’s been a dream come true. I can’t even begin to describe my gratitude to the show and to all the people who gave this opportunity to me 🥹 Thank you to those people, you know who you are 😉

Hosting is such a big passion for me and has been for a long time. I can’t wait to be doing more in the near future and I’m excited to dive into some of the opportunities I have coming up! I’m truly so excited!! 

This performance is called ‘A week in the life of a DWTS pro’ and it’s honestly my fav part of the Tour this year, and where I feel most myself actually!! I love feeling the audience and engaging in their energy, sometimes mixing it up a little, and it’s honestly all very true to what we do in the TV show! So I love getting the opportunity to share our POV with everyone who came to see us. @nopenother created a masterpiece and I’m so thankful to be part of this incredible tour every night. I can’t believe how @dancingwiththestars has changed my life, I love this family I landed in! 
Please let me know what you think of this!!! @dwtstourofficial

Now that Instagram is back up… Happy women’s day!!! I’m so lucky to be surrounded by all these inspiring and powerful women, including my sister and my mum ❤️ Hug your women today and everyday! GIRL POWER!!!! #spicegirlsforever

We finished the tour a couple of days ago and I miss it so much! Thank you @nopenother for creating this beautiful show, I hope you are so proud of it. Thank you Jared and Nikole for believing in us and allowing us to do this. And thank you to my awesome cast mates, I love you guys heaps!!! Grateful for so many beautiful memories this tour!

Alfonso is so passionate about learning as much as he can about dance, and growing in his understanding of it all. It’s so admirable. Meet the lovely people here at @ovaeggfreezing where I am freezing my eggs. The nurses and doctors here have made this journey so comforting, I feel really supported and taken care of. I’m very grateful that this process is available for people, whatever the individual reason may be, for me it’s about taking control of my future and preserving my options. Having the ability to know where your body is at while working through life is very valuable, and this facility has allowed for so many people to be blessed with future options. 
I believe many who are wondering about this process may not know where to start and may have some questions. This is the reason I wanted to share a bit about what it entails. I really love to support women as much as I can, whatever your reasoning and choices are for freezing your eggs, I respect them. I’m grateful to those who respect mine too, it does take a lot of thought, courage and consideration but ultimately this is giving me peace of mind. And my friends here at OVA could not be more attentive and professional 🫶🏻 I’ll be sharing some stories this week, I’ll do an IG live with an OVA fertility nurse at some point while also checking out Chicago cause I love this city! #ovaeggfreezing

Hi! As some of you may know, I’ve been freezing my eggs for this past 10 days here in Chicago at @ovaeggfreezing and while my decision to do this for myself personally was an easy one, the decision to share it was much harder for me and I almost didn’t. But now after initially sharing it a few days ago, I’m SO glad I didn’t let any fear of judgment allow me not be openly honestly and talk about a really important topic that I feel should be ok to talk about. Thank you for allowing me a space to do that, and I have really have tried to respond to as many questions that I received as possible. I found that egg freezing is a topic that many people have questions about so I decided to film this video with Whitney and Cassidy so you can hear more about the process and they can answer some questions you may have, this is part 1 of the vid, part 2 is on my page also. I’m doing this so I can hopefully play a small part in normalizing this topic and hopefully someone out there can feel helped by this conversation. Love you guys 🙏🏻❤️

Part two of the video I just posted, we are talking about Egg Freezing, which is currently what I’m doing. I’m talking with the lovely Cassidy Coughlin and Whitney Angel of @ovaeggfreezing. My procedure is tomorrow and I am not nervous because of the incredible staff here at OVA who have been nothing but kind, thoughtful and supportive, from day one everything was explained to me and they made sure I understood all the steps. From the caring phones calls to the reminder texts and full communication, I don’t know how they do it. Thank you Dr. Kaplan, Colleen Coughlin, and all of the wonderful staff here for guiding me through this life-changing journey with love.

social_posts.post_text:
We are a family ❤️ sharing the best years of my life with my stunning sisters and brothers on stage has been the privilege of a lifetime. Dancing for Len Goodman tonight all as one was an honor and a moment I think I’ll never forget, making time stand still for me. I looked up at the ceiling, looked at all the parts of the ballroom so I can remember every part of my time here. Grateful is too small a word. 
Thankful that this moment of Bruno and I was captured, this was after Len’s tribute dance was over and Bruno’s reaction really got me. Life is short. Spend it with those who make your life magic ❤️

Goofing around with friends 🙌🏻🩷 These are the moments I’ll remember forever. Backstage laughing, driving the production crazy because I’m doing something stupid (sorry guys!), lifting each other up, even the stress of choreographing!!!!! I love to be in the thick of that pressure I guess!! It’s absolutely hard at times and filled with obstacles, but I wouldn’t change my days on this show with these people for the world and at the end of the day I’m still completely in love with what I do. I hope to feel this lucky in all my life, though of course I’m totally aware of how rare this is. Love this family of mine. 🤩🙌🏻
